    <section id="id1165485278453">
      <title>LEADERSHIP AND MANAGEMENT</title>
      <list id="id1165484898434" list-type="bulleted">
        <item><emphasis effect="bold">A leader</emphasis> is someone with a talent for leading others. He walks ahead; he must point the way and move in the right direction.</item>
      </list>
      <list id="id1165485247630" list-type="bulleted">
        <item><emphasis effect="bold">A manager</emphasis> is the leader of a business. Apart from guiding his colleagues, he makes important decisions to steer the company’s future.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1165485344154">Basically a leader and a manager fulfil the same functions as the <emphasis effect="bold">captain </emphasis>of<emphasis effect="bold"/>a rugby or netball team. Those in leading positions want to lead a winning team, and they realise that they are largely responsible for their team’s success.</para>
    </section>
