    <section id="id1165486411031">
      <title>[LO 3.2]</title>
      <para id="id1165485144110">Each management style is determined by the manager’s view of his workers. Write down only the corresponding numbers in the column below the appropriate heading.</para>
      <list id="id1165485328006" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>Workers are lazy by nature, therefore they will avoid working if they can.</item>
        <item>Workers want to be treated as human beings.</item>
        <item>Workers enjoy hard work if they see that they have achieved something worthwhile.</item>
        <item>Workers will do nothing without extra pay.</item>
        <item>Workers’ social needs are just as important as their financial needs.</item>
        <item>Workers prefer to be left to themselves so that they can show the boss how good they are.</item>
        <item>Workers will rather leave it to the manager to solve problems, so that somebody else can be blamed if something goes wrong.</item>
        <item>Workers are people who want to be noticed.</item>
        <item>The manager may not think that the members of his staff are important, but he will at least try to make them feel important.</item>
        <item>Workers will plan the work themselves and check to see if it has been done properly.</item>
        <item>The manager will encourage workers to show initiative and trust them to carry on with their work.</item>
        <item>Workers cannot think for themselves, due to insufficient education/training/experience.</item>
      </list>
